  "prompt": "What are some examples of websites with great design?",
  "response": "There are many websites known for their excellent design, reflecting creativity, functionality, and user experience. Here are some examples from various categories:\n\n1. **Apple (apple.com):**\n   - Known for its minimalist design, intuitive navigation, and high-quality imagery, Apple's website exemplifies sleek and effective design aesthetics.\n\n2. **Airbnb (airbnb.com):**\n   - Airbnb's website features a clean and inviting design, with a strong emphasis on visuals to showcase properties and experiences, as well as a user-friendly interface.\n\n3. **Dropbox (dropbox.com):**\n   - Dropbox uses a straightforward, clean, and professional design that communicates its brand effectively, focusing on usability and easy navigation.\n\n4. **Spotify (spotify.com):**\n   - Spotify combines striking visuals with smooth functionality. Its design is vibrant and matches its brand's energetic identity while maintaining ease of use.\n\n5. **Medium (medium.com):**\n   - Medium employs a clean, distraction-free design that enhances readability and focuses on content, while also offering intuitive navigation for seamless user experience.\n\n6. **Squarespace (squarespace.com):**\n   - Known for powerful design tools, Squarespace itself has a stunning site that showcases its templates, emphasizing creativity and professional appearance.\n\n7. **Wired (wired.com):**\n   - Wired's website uses a modern design with engaging visuals and a dynamic layout that keeps users engaged with its content.\n\n8. **Awwwards (awwwards.com):**\n   - As a site that celebrates design excellence, Awwwards features innovative and inspiring designs from across the web, often highlighting creative and cutting-edge digital experiences.\n\n9. **Behance (behance.net):**\n   - Behance's portfolio platform is designed to showcase artists' works beautifully, using a grid layout and seamless motion effects that highlight creativity and professionalism.\n\n10. **TED (ted.com):**\n    - TED's website balances multimedia content with an organized and aesthetically pleasing design, making it easy for users to find and engage with talks.\n\nThese websites are known for integrating strong visual design, intuitive user experience, and innovative use of technology, making them leaders in their respective categories.",
